						<br />

			<small class="commentmetadata"><a href="#comment-248399" title="">March 30th, 2011 at 12:26 am</a> </small>

			<p>These look delicious! But a note about espresso: to make an even better taste, add the espresso to warm milk rather than water. Espresso goes bad (all bitter&#8230;it&#8217;s supposed to be sweet, caramely, and *lightly* bitter) within 10 seconds unless added to warm-hot lactose. I would suggest skim milk, as it isn&#8217;t as thick as 2%. I gotta say, these look incredible!</p>

		</li>

	
	
