						<br />

			<small class="commentmetadata"><a href="#comment-525087" title="">October 9th, 2011 at 10:43 pm</a> </small>

			<p>Laura &#8211; you may want to reduce the amount of flour you&#8217;re using?  Shortbread cookies ARE dry, but they shouldn&#8217;t be that dry.  Keep in mind that 2 cups are not the same the world over &#8211; flour density will determine if you are using more or less flour than I do, so I&#8217;d try scooping the flour, then shaking it back into the flour container and doing that a couple of times before scooping your flour to measure for the recipe.</p>
